pull_request.title: fix(agent/agentscripts): show informative error for ErrWaitDelay
pull_request.body:
This PR makes it so that Coder shows an informative error instead of `exec.ErrWaitDelay` to users. To ease with discovery, and informing the user that something is wrong, the message is printed to both the script log (db/file) and to the agent log.

Fixes #10400

 process may now have been terminated. Consider using a separate \"coder_script\" for the service, see https://coder.com/docs/v2/latest/templates/troubleshooting#startup-script-issues for more information." ...

issue.title: Coder CLI Remove Template Version
issue.body:
Hi,
We're managing multiple templates, and for some templates, we're having too many versions, so we thought of deleting the older versions.
What it would be a good idea, is to add a `Template Version Deletion ` feature, especially from the CLI, like `coder templates versions remove TEMPLATE_NAME  --name VERSION_NAME`.

issue.title: Assign and display specfic user(s) as the template admin

labels.name: stale
labels.description: This issue is like stale bread.

issue.body:
Any thoughts on assigning  template admin(s) per template

1. Users with member roles should be able to see who is the admin for each template.
2. Only the template admin can push changes to the template
3. It will help members to contact the right person if anything is wrong with a template
4. distribute template maintenance work between the team members

Context: I have multiple templates, one of them managed by another member. If that template has a problem, I do not want other members to contact me and instead contact the right person. That person should be visible on the template page in the template information.

[Slack Message](https://codercom.slack.com/archives/CJURPL8DN/p1682580072843639)

Related to #6452
